= Railfrog

Railfrog:http://railfrog.com is a user-friendly, open-source website deployment and 
content management system built with Ruby on Rails, producing well structured and 
standards-compliant pages with Web 2.0 goodness. Railfrog makes it easy for developers, 
designers, webmasters, or just about anyone else to deploy and manage a website.


== Installation notes

=== ... for existing applications

1. Install Rails Engines:

  ruby script/plugin install http://svn.rails-engines.org/engines/trunk/

2. Install acts_as_nested_set plugin:

  ruby script/plugin install http://svn.rubyonrails.org/rails/plugins/acts_as_nested_set/

3. Install upload_progress plugin:

  ruby script/plugin install http://svn.rubyonrails.org/rails/plugins/upload_progress/

4. Install Railfrog plugin:

  ruby script/plugin install https://svn.versiondude.net/railfrog/cms/railfrog/trunk/engine railfrog

5. Add following line to config/environment.rb, just after the require of Rails' boot file:

  require File.join(File.dirname(__FILE__), '../vendor/plugins/engines/boot')

6. Add following line to config/routes.rb, just after first line:
  
  map.from_plugin :railfrog

7. Run:

  ruby script/generate plugin_migration && rake db:migrate

=== ... new application

1. Grab our empty Rails 2.0.2 application with installed Railfrog:
  
  svn co https://svn.versiondude.net/railfrog/cms/railfrog/trunk/ref_app railfrog

2. Run:

  rake railfrog:site:load SITE=db/sites/railfrog

